    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-02-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-02-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="84"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                <head>84. Memorandum for the Record, February 27<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d84fn1">Status of interest on testing, March shot, and U.S.S.R.
                        acceptance of test ban treaty by <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>
                        meeting participants. Secret. 1 p. National Defense University, <persName
                            corresp="#p_TMD_1">Taylor</persName> Papers.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-02-27">February 27, 1962</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d84-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d84-1"/>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>NCS Meeting, 27 February 1962</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. For testing:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RD_1">Rusk</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MRS_1"
                        >McNamara</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_GRL_1">Gilpatric</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_LLL_1">Lemnitzer</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_FWC_1">Foster</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SGT_1"
                        >Seaborg</persName>, VP.</p>
                <p>2. Against:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SAE_1">Stevenson</persName>, Moral and political factors.
                    Equality favors disarmament. Peace package.</p>
                <p>3. For March shot:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_FWC_1">Foster</persName>, VP.</p>
                <p>4. Against March shot:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RD_1">Rusk</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SGT_1"
                        >Seaborg</persName> (marginal), HA (marginal; picture)</p>
                <p>5. <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss> acceptance of ban treaty.</p>
                <quote>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">a</hi>. Stop: <persName corresp="#p_RD_1">Rusk</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_MRS_1">McNamara</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_GRL_1">Gilpatric</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_FWC_1"
                            >Foster</persName>.</p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">b</hi>. Continue: <persName corresp="#p_LLL_1"
                            >Lemnitzer</persName>.</p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">c</hi>. Revise treaty: <persName corresp="#p_DA_1"
                            >Dean</persName>.</p>
                </quote>
                <p>6. Timing considered.</p>
                <quote>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">a</hi>. Minimum delay after announcement: <persName
                            corresp="#p_MER_1">Murrow</persName>.</p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">b</hi>. Announce intention, then wait several weeks to see
                        effect at Geneva.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">M.D.T.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
